@cindex ssh
@cindex jail

@process{Ssh} (see @code{man ssh(1)}) 
is used to exchange meta-data and archives files by
using a ``chroot'' jail for each collection account, that 
@procScriptsBind{} cache and cvsroot directories.
The @sc{Sshd}'s configuration files given bellow are generated by 
@procScriptsInitRemovePurge{} and @procScriptsNewFreeClean{} scripts.

Process conceptual model:

@image{mediatex-figures/ssh,,,,}

@itemize @bullet
@item Events in
@table @code
@item @eventToolsSshConnect
from @procToolsCvs
@item @eventToolsSshCopy 
from @procClientMisc
@end table

@item Data in
@table @file
@item /etc/ssh/sshd_config
@end table
@example
...
# <<<mdtx-*
Match user mdtx-*
          ChrootDirectory /var/cache/mediatex/mdtx/jail
          X11Forwarding no
          AllowTcpForwarding no
# mdtx-*>>>
@end example
@table @file
@item /var/cache/mediatex/mdtx/jail/etc/group
@end table
@example
root:x:0:
www-data:x:33:www-data
mdtx:x:120:www-data
mdtx_md:x:123:mdtx,www-data
mdtx-COLL:x:124:www-data,mdtx
@end example
@table @file
@item /var/cache/mediatex/mdtx/jail/etc/password
@end table
